From 7dafdfcd200f3ee877c11246ec90ee8d7c8a6c61 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Andy Vandijck <andyvand@gmail.com>
Date: Sun, 12 Jul 2026 23:42:25 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Restore Windows XP support in wxMSW

Allow wxMSW to build and run under Windows XP again by loading Vista+
functions dynamically (a static import prevents the binary from loading
on XP) and guarding newer SDK symbols behind _WIN32_WINNT checks.

- Add wxKernel32Dll in uilocale.cpp to resolve the kernel32 NLS functions
  (GetLocaleInfoEx, CompareStringEx, Get/SetThreadPreferredUILanguages,
  GetUserDefaultLocaleName) once, falling back to the LCID-based APIs under
  XP; back-define LOCALE_SNAME and LOCALE_SSHORTESTDAYNAME* for XP SDKs.
- Add wxDrawThemeTextEx() in uxtheme.cpp which loads DrawThemeTextEx()
  dynamically and falls back to DrawThemeText() under XP; use it in
  renderer.cpp and darkmode.cpp so modern systems keep custom text colours.
  Back-define DTTOPTS/DTT_CALLBACK_PROC and MENU_BARITEM in uxtheme.h.
- Load SetCurrentProcessExplicitAppUserModelID (from shell32), RegDeleteKeyEx
  and GetProductInfo (in wxGetOsDescription) dynamically, keeping full
  behaviour on modern systems.
- Restore the wxHAS_MSW_TASKDIALOG mechanism so task dialogs are compiled
  out under XP, and guard taskdlg.h/taskdlg.cpp with the same condition.
- Guard gesture/touch/pointer handling, TBCDRF_USECDCOLORS, the balloon
  icon, GR_*_PEAK, SysLink default colours and the dark-mode submenu arrow
  with _WIN32_WINNT checks.
- Guard wxUSE_IFILEOPENDIALOG on _WIN32_WINNT >= 0x0600 and only require a
  v6 comctl32 manifest on Vista and later.
- Fix the XP/MinGW build: include gethwnd.h unconditionally in dirdlg.cpp
  (wxGetHWND is used outside the IFileOpenDialog path, disabled under XP),
  store the Direct2D IUnknown refcount as LONG so Interlocked{Increment,
  Decrement}() accept it, and silence an unused totalPages warning in
  printps.cpp when wxUSE_PROGRESSDLG is 0.

Co-Authored-By: Rafael Kitover <rkitover@gmail.com>
Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
